<p class="">We are not asking the Prime Minister to embark upon any statement of policy, in view of the disturbance in many people's minds at the course of events; but in view of the fact that a disposal of these 50,000 prisoners of war is now a major political problem, is the Prime Minister satisfied that full consultations are taking place meanwhile between the United States Government, the British Government and the other Governments interested in this matter, and that they are taking place at Ministerial level?</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
